The FT-IR spectra of Cu: Eu MOF are shown in Fig. 3D. The vibration band of -COO- is red-shifted from 1430 cm−1 of IPA to 1396 cm−1 of Eu MOF and 1388 cm−1 of Cu: Eu MOF and the asymmetric stretching vibration band of-COO- at 1538 cm−1 is enhanced,[

                           29

                        ] Due to the coordination of carboxyl groups with Cu2+ and Eu3+, the strong band of C = O stretching vibration is red-shifted from 1747 cm−1 of IPA to 1605 cm −1 of Cu: Eu MOF. In addition, as shown in Fig. S3A, the UV–visible absorption spectra of pure Eu MOF (a) and Cu: Eu MOF (b) were compared. Eu MOF shows a strong absorption band around 350 nm, which may be attributed to the π − π* transition of the ligand (IPA) [29]； Due to the doping of Cu2+, Cu: Eu MOF produces a new absorption band at 450 nm, which lays a foundation for the increase of effective spectral overlap and effective quenching. The above results prove the successful preparation of Cu: Eu MOF.
